entry.title: Lords of the iteration
entry.summary: We introduce several properties of forcing notions which imply that their lambda-support iterations are lambda-proper. Our methods and techniques refine those studied in math.LO/9906024, math.LO/0210205, math.LO/0508272 and math.LO/0605067, covering some new forcing notions (though the exact relation of the new properties to the old ones remains undecided).
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Set theory and its applications, 287-330, Contemp. Math., 533, 2011

entry.title: Isolating Cardinal Invariants
entry.summary: There is an optimal way to increase certain cardinal invariants of the continuum.

entry.title: A remark on utility streams
entry.summary: We consider arbitrarily long, but finite utility streams, and some appropriate axioms.

entry.title: Toolbox
entry.summary: Contains various tools for preferential and related logics

entry.title: Descriptive inner model theory
entry.summary: A paper for general audience about descriptive inner model theory.

entry.title: Woodin's surgery method
entry.summary: In this short paper we give an overview of Woodin's surgery method.

entry.title: On a question of Zadrozny
entry.summary: We answer a question of Zadrozny.

entry.title: Zero-one laws for graphs with edge probabilities decaying with distance. Part II
entry.summary: This is the second part of math.LO/9606226.

entry.title: QL(C^n) determines n
entry.summary: This addendum to math.LO/0412144 shows that the set of tautological quantum logical propositional formulas for a finite dimensional vector space C^n is different for every n, affirmatively answering a question posed therein.

entry.title: More about lambda-support iterations of <lambda-complete forcing notions
entry.summary: This article continues Ros{\l}anowski and Shelah math.LO/9906024, math.LO/0508272, math.LO/0210205, math.LO/0611131 and math.LO/0605067. We introduce here a new property of <lambda-strategically complete forcing notions which implies that their lambda-support iterations do not collapse lambda^+ (for a strongly inaccessible cardinal lambda).
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Archive for Mathematical Logic: Volume 52, Issue 5 (2013), Page 603-629

entry.title: Chasing Silver
entry.summary: Answering a question of the first author stated in [math.LO/0507519, 0.2] we show that limits of CS iterations of n$-Silver forcing notion have the n-localization property.

entry.title: Existence of EF-equivalent Non Isomorphic Models
entry.summary: We prove the existence of pairs of models of the same cardinality lambda which are very equivalent according to EF games, but not isomorphic. We continue the paper math.LO/0404222, but we don't rely on it.

entry.title: The last forcing standing with diamonds
entry.summary: This article continues Roslanowski and Shelah math.LO/9906024 and 1105.6049 We introduce here yet another property of (<lambda)-strategically complete forcing notions which implies that their lambda-support iterations do not collapse lambda^+.

entry.title: Filter-Laver Measurability
entry.summary: We study sigma-ideals and regularity properties related to the "filter-Laver" and "dual-filter-Laver" forcing partial orders. An important innovation which enables this study is a dichotomy theorem proved recently by Miller [1]. [1] Arnold Miller, "Hechler and Laver Trees", Preprint 2012 (arXiv:1204.5198 [math.LO]).

entry.title: Generating ultrafilters in a reasonable way
entry.summary: We continue investigations of reasonable ultrafilters on uncountable cardinals defined in Shelah math.LO/0407498 and studied also in math.LO/0605067. We introduce a general scheme of generating a filter on lambda from filters on smaller sets and we investigate the combinatorics of objects obtained this way.

entry.title: No limit model in inaccessible
entry.summary: Our aim is to improve the negative results i.e. non-existence of limit models, and the failure of the generic pair property from math.LO/0609636 to inaccessible lambda as promised there. The motivation is that in [Sh:F756] the positive results are for lambda measurable hence inaccessible, whereas in math.LO/0609636 in the negative results obtained only on non-strong limit cardinals.

entry.title: A note on canonical functions
entry.summary: We construct a generic extension in which the aleph_2 nd canonical function on aleph_1 exists.

entry.title: A short proof of the irreflexivity conjecture
entry.summary: Gives a short proof of Dehornoy's latest result. The same simple argument (and more) was discovered by Laver's student Larue.

entry.title: On Gödel's second incompleteness theorem
entry.summary: A very short proof of G\"odel's second incompleteness theorem (for set theory, second order arithmetic etc.)

entry.title: On Braid Words and Irreflexivity
entry.summary: The purpose of this note is to prove irreflexivity, and hence the linear ordering, in ZFC, without some of the machinery used by Dehornoy.

entry.title: The Cardinality of the second uniform indiscernible
entry.summary: When the second uniform indiscernible is $\aleph_{2}$, the Martin-Solovay tree only constructs countably many reals; this resolves a number of open questions in descriptive set theory.

entry.title: Some Natural Internal Forcing Schemata Extending ZFC
entry.summary: We give arguments for and prove the consistency of some internal forcing axioms.

entry.title: The additivity of porosity ideals
entry.summary: We show that several sigma-ideals related to porous sets have additivity omega_1 and cofinality 2^omega. This answers a question addressed by Miroslav Repick'y.

entry.title: A New Proof of Kunen's Inconsistency
entry.summary: Using elementary pcf, we show that there is no $j:V\to M,$ $M$ transitive, $j\lambda =\lambda >crit(j),$ $j^{\prime \prime}\lambda \in M.$

entry.title: Is game semantics necessary?
entry.summary: We discuss the extent to which game semantics is implicit in the formalism of linear logic and in the intuitions underlying linear logic.

entry.title: On closed unbounded sets consisting of former regulars
entry.summary: We give the optimal conditions for the existence of a club consisting of former regular over an inaccessible and a measurable. The foricing construction based on iteration of distributive posets.

entry.title: Small forcings and Cohen reals
entry.summary: We prove it consistent relative to ZFC that all nontrivial forcings of size $\aleph _1$ add a Cohen real.

entry.title: A complete Boolean algebra that has no proper atomless complete subalgebra
entry.summary: There exists a complete atomless Boolean algebra that has no proper atomless complete subalgebra.

entry.title: On Countably Closed Complete Boolean Algebras
entry.summary: It is unprovable that every complete subalgebra of a countably closed complete Boolean algebra is countably closed.

entry.title: The A,B,C of pcf: a companion to pcf theory, Part I
entry.summary: This is a survey paper of Shelah's pcf theory. In this part the theory is developed up to the pcf theorem.

entry.title: Some interesting problems
entry.summary: This is an update of my problem list.

entry.title: On full Souslin trees
entry.summary: In this note we answer a question of Kunen (15.13 [Mi91]) showing that it is consistent that there are full Souslin trees

entry.title: Subalgebras of Cohen algebras need not be Cohen
entry.summary: We give an example of a regular and complete subalgebra of a Cohen algebra which is not Cohen.

entry.title: Club does not imply the existence of a Suslin tree
entry.summary: We prove that club does not imply the existence of a Suslin tree, so answering a question of I. Juhasz.

entry.title: Superdestructibility: a dual to Laver indestructibility
entry.summary: After small forcing, any < kappa-closed forcing will destroy the supercompactness, even the strong compactness, of kappa .

entry.title: A universal Polish G-space
entry.summary: If G is a Polish group, then there is a Polish G-space X which is universal among Polish G-spaces with respect to continuous G-embeddings.

entry.title: $\square_κ^{<ω}$ holds in $L[{\vec E}]$
entry.summary: Square-kappa-finite, the finite family version of weak square, holds at all cardinals kappa in the Mitchell-Steel inner models.

entry.title: A polarized partition relation and failure of GCH
entry.summary: The main result is that for lambda strong limit singular failing the continuum hypothesis (i.e. 2^lambda > lambda^+), a polarized partition theorem holds.

entry.title: A Survey of Ultraproduct Constructions in General Topology
entry.summary: We survey various attempts to transport the ultraproduct construction from the realm of model theory to that of general topology.

entry.title: Constructing strongly equivalent nonisomorphic models for unsuperstable theories, Part C
entry.summary: In this paper we prove a strong nonstructure theorem for kappa (T)-saturated models of a stable theory T with dop.

entry.title: Topological density of ccc Boolean algebras - every cardinality occurs.
entry.summary: For every uncountable cardinal mu there is a ccc Boolean algebra whose topological density is mu .

entry.title: Aspects of Computability in Physics
entry.summary: This paper reviews connections between physics and computation, and explores their implications. The main topics are computational "hardness" of physical systems, computational status of fundamental theories, quantum computation, and the Universe as a computer.

entry.title: Luzin and anti-Luzin almost disjoint families
entry.summary: Under MA_{omega_1} every uncountable almost disjoint family is either anti-Luzin or has an uncountable Luzin subfamily. This fails under CH. Related properties are also investigated.

entry.title: Vaught's conjecture on analytic sets
entry.summary: This paper obtains an algebraic characterization of the Polish groups that satisfy Vaught's conjecture on $\bf{\Sigma}^1_1$ sets.

entry.title: The condition in the Trichotomy Theorem is optimal
entry.summary: We show that the assumption lambda > kappa^+ in the Trichotomy Theorem cannot be relaxed to lambda > kappa .

entry.title: Some results on combinators in the system TRC
entry.summary: We investigate the system TRC of combinatory logic that is equiconsistent with New Foundations. We prove that various unstratified combinators do not exist in TRC.

entry.title: Covering of the null ideal may have countable cofinality
entry.summary: We prove that it is consistent that the covering of the ideal of measure zero sets has countable cofinality.

entry.title: Intersection of less than continuum ultrafilters may have measure zero
entry.summary: The goal of this paper is to prove the theorem in the title.

entry.title: Remarks on the intersection of filters
entry.summary: The existence of an uncountable family of nonmeager filter whose intersection is meager is consistent with MA(Suslin)

entry.title: Splitting number
entry.summary: It is shown that it is consistent with ZFC that every uncountable set can be continuously mapped onto a splitting family.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society, 125 (1997), 2141-2145

entry.title: Not every gamma-set is strongly meager
entry.summary: We present two constructions of gamma-sets which are large in sense of category.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Contemporary Mathematics, vol. 192, American Mathematical Society, 1996, pp. 25-29

entry.title: On cofinality of the smallest covering of the real line by meager sets II
entry.summary: We study the ideal of meager sets and related ideals.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society 123 (1995), no. 6, 1879-1885

entry.title: Filters and games
entry.summary: We obtain game-theoretic characterizations for meagerness and rareness of filters on a countable set.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society 123 (1995), 2529-2534

entry.title: Propositional Manifolds
entry.summary: This paper was withdrawn by the author due to an edition's rights

entry.title: Invariants of Measure and Category
entry.summary: A survey of recent results concerning cardinal invariants of measure and category. Submitted as a chapter of the upcoming Handbook of Set Theory.

entry.title: Boolean algebras with prescribed topological densities
entry.summary: We give a simplified proof of a theorem of M. Rabus and S. Shelah claiming that for each cardinal mu there is a c.c.c Boolean algebra with topological density mu.

entry.title: Showing OCA in Pmax-style extensions
entry.summary: We give a proof that OCA holds in the Pmax extension of L(R). The proof is general enough to be adapted to most Pmax variations.

entry.title: A continuation of [DjSh:691]
entry.summary: We continue to investigate club guessing (see [Sh:g, Ch III] and [Sh:e, Ch VI]), continuing Dzamonja and Shelah [DjSh:691]

entry.title: Cardinal invariants b_kappa and t_kappa
entry.summary: This paper studies cardinal invariants b_kappa and t_kappa, the natural generalizations of the invariants b and t to a regular cardinal kappa.

entry.title: No bound for the first fixed point
entry.summary: Our aim is to show that it is impossible to find a bound for the power of the first fixed point of the aleph function.

entry.title: Superatomic Boolean Algebras: maximal rigidity
entry.summary: We prove that for any superatomic Boolean Algebra of cardinality >beth_omega there is an automorphism moving uncountably many atoms. Similarly for larger cardinals. Any of those results are essentially best possible.

entry.title: The relative consistency of g<cf(Sym(omega))
entry.summary: We prove the consistency result from the title. By forcing we construct a model of g=aleph_1, b=cf(Sym(omega))=aleph_2.

entry.title: Martin's Axiom is Consistent with the Existence of Nowhere Trivial Automorphisms
entry.summary: Martin's Axiom does not imply that all automorphisms of P(N)/[N]^{<aleph_0} are somewhere trivial.

entry.title: On Whitehead precovers
entry.summary: It is proved undecidable in ZFC + GCH whether every Z-module has a^{perp} {Z}-precover.

entry.title: Fields with pseudo-exponentiation
entry.summary: We study the structure of an algebraically closed field with extra function resembling the classical exponentiation on complex numbers.

entry.title: Perfectly meager sets and universally null sets
entry.summary: We will show that there is no ZFC example of a set distinguishing between universally null and perfectly meager sets.

entry.title: You Can Enter Cantor's Paradise
entry.summary: This paper is based on the talk given by the author after he received the International Bolyai Prize in Mathematics (on November 4, 2000 in Budapest, Hungary).

entry.title: A partition relation using strongly compact cardinals
entry.summary: If kappa is strongly compact, lambda > kappa is regular, then (2^{< lambda})^+ --> (lambda+eta)^2_theta holds for eta,theta<kappa.

entry.title: P not= NP for infinite time Turing machines
entry.summary: We state a version of the P=?NP problem for infinite time Turing machines. It is observed that P not= NP for this version.

entry.title: Duality Chipped
entry.summary: Whenever I is a projectively generated projectively defined sigma ideal on the reals, if ZFC+large cardinals proves cov(I)=continuum then ZFC+large cardinals proves non(I)<aleph four.

entry.title: Countable Support Iteration Revisited
entry.summary: Whenever P is a proper definable forcing for adding a real, the countable support iteration of P has all the preservation properties it can possibly have, within a wide syntactically identified class of properties.

entry.title: Remarks on small sets of reals
entry.summary: We show that the Dual Borel Conjecture implies that ${\mathfrak d}> \aleph_1$ and find some topological characterizations of perfectly meager and universally meager sets.

entry.title: On Independent Representation
entry.summary: The paper has been withdrawn.

entry.title: Specializing Aronszajn trees by countable approximations
entry.summary: We show that there are proper forcings based upon countable trees of creatures that specialize a given Aronszajn tree.

entry.title: A simple proof of Σ^1_3 correctness of K
entry.summary: We present a simple and purely combinatorial proof of Steel's result according to which the core model is \Sigma^1_3 correct under the appropriate hypotheses.

entry.title: Strongly meager sets of size continuum
entry.summary: We construct several models where there are no strongly meager sets of size continuum. In particular, there are no such sets in the Laver's model.

entry.title: Logical Dreams
entry.summary: We discuss the past and future of set theory, axiom systems and independence results. We deal in particular with cardinal arithmetic.

entry.title: Martin's Axiom and Maximal Orthogonal Families
entry.summary: It is shown that Martin's Axiom for sigma-centred partial orders implies that every maximal orthogonal family in R^N is of size 2^{aleph_0}

entry.title: A partition theorem for scattered order types
entry.summary: If phi is a scattered order type, mu a cardinal, then there exists a scattered order type psi such that psi->[phi]^1_{mu,aleph_0} holds.

entry.title: Games with creatures
entry.summary: Many forcing notions obtained using the creature technology are naturally connected with certain integer games.

entry.title: Complexity and ordinary life, and some mathematics in both
entry.summary: This is a very basic introduction to some notions related to logic and complexity.

entry.title: Hyperquasivarieties
entry.summary: In the paper we consider the notion of hyper-quasi-identities and hyperquasivarieties as a generalization of the concept of quasi-identity and quasivariety invented by A. I. Mal'cev.

entry.title: Boolos-style proofs of limitative theorems
entry.summary: Boolos's proof of incompleteness is extended straightforwardly to yield simple ``diagonalization-free'' proofs of some classical limitative theorems of logic.

entry.title: Polynomial Functions on a Central Relation
entry.summary: We show that the algebra $\mathbf{R} = \bigl(R; \wedge, \veebar, 0, \bar{f}_i(x) (i \in I)\bigr)$ is central polynomially complete and finite.

entry.title: Model theory of valued fields
entry.summary: We give a proposal for future development of the model theory of valued fields. We also summarize some recent results on p-adic numbers.
entry.arxiv:comment: To appear in Proceedings of Ravello model theory conference

entry.title: On the structure of stationary sets
entry.summary: We isolate several classes of stationary sets of kappa^omega and investigate implications among them. Under a large cardinal assumption, we prove a structure theorem for stationary sets.

entry.title: Complete ccc Boolean algebras, the order sequential topology, and a problem of von Neumann
entry.summary: It is consistent that every weakly distributive complete ccc Boolean algebra carries a strictly positive Maharam submeasure.

entry.title: Long low iterations
entry.summary: We try to control many cardinal characteristics by working with a notion of orthogonality between two families of forcings. We show that b^+<g is consistent

entry.title: Simple Complete Boolean Algebras
entry.summary: For every regular cardinal kappa there exists a simple complete Boolean algebra with kappa generators.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society, 129:543--549, 2001

entry.title: The depth of ultraproducts of Boolean Algebras
entry.summary: We show in ZFC, that the depth of ultraproducts of Boolean Algebras may be bigger than the ultraproduct of the depth of those Boolean Algebras.

entry.title: Forcing with quotients
entry.summary: We study an extensive connection between factor forcings of Borel subsets of Polish spaces modulo a sigma-ideal, and factor forcings of subsets of countable sets modulo an ideal.

entry.title: Quantum logic as motivated by quantum computing
entry.summary: We explore a connection between quantum logic and quantum computing.

entry.title: Two preservation theorems
entry.summary: I prove preservation theorems for countable support iteration of proper forcing concerning certain classes of capacities and submeasures. New examples of forcing notions and connections with measure theory are included.

entry.title: Potential theory and forcing
entry.summary: We isolate a combinatorial property of capacities leading to a construction of proper forcings. Then we show that many classical capacities such as the Newtonian capacity satisfy the property.

entry.title: Minimal bounded index subgroup for dependent theories
entry.summary: For a dependent theory T, in C_T for every type definable group G, the intersection of type definable subgroups with bounded index is a type definable subgroup with bounded index.

entry.title: The Erdos-Rado arrow for singular cardinals
entry.summary: We prove that if cf(lambda) > aleph_0 and 2^{cf(lambda)}<lambda, then lambda->(lambda,omega+1)^2.

entry.title: Intermediate logics and factors of the Medvedev lattice
entry.summary: We investigate the initial segments of the Medvedev lattice as Brouwer algebras, and study the propositional logics connected to them.

entry.title: The finite intervals of the Muchnik lattice
entry.summary: We characterize the finite intervals of the Muchnik lattice by proving that they are a certain proper subclass of the finite distributive lattices.

entry.title: Domain closure conditions and definability preservation
entry.summary: We examine problems due to lack of domain closure and definability preservation

entry.title: An application of CAT
entry.summary: We comment on a question of Justin Moore on colourings of pairs of nodes in an Aronszajn tree and solve an instance of it.

entry.title: A general Stone representation theorem
entry.summary: This note contains a Stone-style representation theorem for compact Hausdorff spaces.

entry.title: A Note on Generic Types
entry.summary: In a stable abelian group, we characterize generic types of cosets of type-definable subgroups.

entry.title: O-minimal spectrum
entry.summary: Let X be a definable sub-set of some o-minimal structure. We study the spectrum of X, in relation with the definability of types.

entry.title: Interpreting Random Hypergraphs in Pseudofinite Fields
entry.summary: We construct a random $n$-hypergraph for every $n$, in a given pseudofinite field.

entry.title: On the equivalence of two quantifier elimination tests
entry.summary: We prove that, for countable languages, two model-theoretic quantifier elimination tests, one proposed by J. R. Shoenfield and the other by L. van den Dries, are equivalent.

entry.title: The Order-Theoretic Structure of Free Heyting Algebras
entry.summary: We find an order-theoretic characterization of the Lindenbaum algebra of intuitionistic propositional logic in n variables.

entry.title: On generically stable types in dependent theories
entry.summary: We develop the theory of generically stable types, independence relation based on nonforking and stable weight in the context of dependent (NIP) theories.

entry.title: Foundations for abstract forcing
entry.summary: The foundations of forcing theory are reworked to streamline the presentation and to show how the most basic results are applicable in very general contexts.

entry.title: Factorization (Splitting)
entry.summary: We show some elementary facts about the semantical analogue of Parikh's Splitting, which we call Factorization.

entry.title: Uniforming n-place functions on ds(alpha)
entry.summary: In this paper the Erdos-Rado theorem is generalized to the class of well founded trees.

entry.title: Successors of Singular Cardinals and Coloring Theorems II
entry.summary: We investigate negative square-brackets partition relations at successors of singular cardinals of countable cofinality. Along the way we prove some club-guessing results.

entry.title: Injectives in residuated algebras
entry.summary: Injectives in several classes of structures associated with logic are characterized. Among the classes considered are residuated lattices, MTL-algebras, IMTL-algebras, BL-algebras, NM-algebras and bounded hoops.

entry.title: A theory of hierarchical consequence and conditionals
entry.summary: We introduce A-ranked preferential structures and combine them with an accessibility relation. This framework allows us to formalize contrary to duty obligations. Representation results are proved.

entry.title: Roadmap for preferential logics
entry.summary: We give an overview of logical and semantical rules for nonmonotonic and related logics.

entry.title: Iteratively algebraic orders
entry.summary: A short proof of a theorem of M.H. Albert, and its application to lattices.

entry.title: Defeasible inheritance systems and reactive diagrams
entry.summary: We give an analysis of defeasible inheritance diagrams, also from the perspective of reactive diagrams.

entry.title: A semantics for obligations
entry.summary: We analyze a number of properties obligations have or should have.

entry.title: K-trivials are NCR
entry.summary: We show that for every K-trivial real X, there is no representation of a continuous probability measure m such that X is 1-random relative to m.

entry.title: Typability in partial groupoids
entry.summary: Adapting a claim of M. Kracht, we establish a characterization of the typable partial applicative algebras.

entry.title: On lambda strongly homogeneity existence for cofinality logics
entry.summary: Let C subset Reg be a non-empty class (of regular cardinal). Then the logic L(Q^{cf}_C) has additional nice properties: it has homogeneous model existence property.

entry.title: On finite imaginaries
entry.summary: We study finite imaginaries in certain valued fields, and prove a conjecture of Cluckers and Denef.

entry.title: Size and Logic
entry.summary: We show how to develop a multitude of rules of nonmonotonic logic from very simple and natural notions of size, using them as building blocks.

entry.title: Independence - revision and defaults
entry.summary: We investigate different aspects of independence here, in the context of theory revision, generalizing slightly work by Chopra, Parikh, and Rodrigues, and in the context of preferential reasoning.

entry.title: Constructive truth and circularity
entry.summary: We propose a constructive interpretation of truth which resolves the standard semantic paradoxes.
entry.arxiv:comment: corrected the discussion of Berry's paradox on page 8

entry.title: Semantic interpolation
entry.summary: We treat interpolation for various logics.

entry.title: On a comparison of Darboux and Riemann integrals in constructive analysis
entry.summary: An example of constructive (in A.A.Markov's sense) real-valued function, which is integrable by Riemann, but is not integrable by Darboux, is constructed.

entry.title: Independence and abstract multiplication
entry.summary: We investigate the notion of independence, which is at the basis of many, seemingly unrelated, properties of logic like Rational Monotony in non-monotonic logics, and interpolation theorems.

entry.title: Club guessing for dummies
entry.summary: We give a direct, detailed and relatively short proof of Shelah's theorem on club guessing sequences on $S^{\mu^+}_\mu$ (for any regular, uncountable cardinal $\mu$).

entry.title: Strong dependence, weight, and measure
entry.summary: I give an account of Shelah's notion of strong dependence, or strong NIP, in terms of suitable generically stable measures, forking, and weight.

entry.title: Exact bounds on epsilon processes
entry.summary: In this paper we show that the lengths of the approximating processes in epsilon substitution method are calculable by ordinal recursions in an optimal way.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Archive for Mathematical Logic vol.50(2011), pp. 445-458

entry.title: Chain homogeneous Souslin algebras
entry.summary: Assuming Jensen's principle diamond-plus we construct Souslin algebras all of whose maximal chains are pairwise isomorphic as total orders, thereby answering questions of Koppelberg and Todorcevic
entry.arxiv:comment: 29 pages, submitted to the Mathematical Logic Quarterly

entry.title: Large weight does not yield an irreducible base
entry.summary: Answering a question of Juhasz, Soukup and Szentmikl\'ossy we show that it is consistent that some first countable space of uncountable weight does not contain an uncountable subspace which has an irreducible base.

entry.title: Inner product space with no ortho-normal basis without choice
entry.summary: We prove in ZF that there is an inner product space, in fact, nicely definable with no orthonormal basis.

entry.title: Artin-Schreier extensions in NIP and simple fields
entry.summary: We show that NIP fields have no Artin-Schreier extension, and that simple fields have only a finite number of them.

entry.title: Forcing Square_{omega_1} with finite conditions
entry.summary: We give a forcing construction of the square principle on omega_1 using forcing with conditions whose domain is finite.

entry.title: Beginning of stability theory for Polish Spaces
entry.summary: We consider stability theory for Polish spaces and more generally for definable structures. We succeed to prove existence of indiscernibles under reasonable conditions.

entry.title: Modules and Infinitary Logics
entry.summary: We prove that the theory of abelian groups and R-modules even in infinitary logic is stable and understood to some extent.

entry.title: Subspaces of an arithmetic universe via type theory
entry.summary: We define the notion of subspace of an arithmetic universe by using its internal dependent type theory.

entry.title: Quelques réflexions inévitables (Some inevitable considerations)
entry.summary: We generalize Fr\'econ's construction of the inevitable radical to groups in stable and even simple theories.

entry.title: Complexity of countable categoricity in finite languages
entry.summary: We study complexity of the index set of countably categorical theories and Ehrenfeucht theories in finite languages.

entry.title: Pity on lambda
entry.summary: We generalize Rothberger's theorem for regular lambda. We prove that the discrepancy between the pseudointersection number and the towering number is limited, under some reasobable assumption

entry.title: A remark on Cantor derivative
entry.summary: It is shown that, modulo an equivalence relation induced by finite correspondences preserving Cantor rank, the class of topological spaces is an integral semi-ring on which the Cantor derivative is precisely a derivation.

entry.title: Categoricity for Patterns of Order 2
entry.summary: A categoricity theorem is established for patterns of resemblance of order 2 showing that the order in which patterns arise in a wide range of hierarchies is the same.

entry.title: Introducing the hardline in proof theory
entry.summary: In this paper we expound some basic ideas of proof theory for theories of ordinals such that there are many stable ordinals below the ordinals.

entry.title: Set-theoretic problems concerning Lindelof spaces
entry.summary: I survey problems concerning Lindelof spaces which have partial set- theoretic solutions.

entry.title: A natural model of the multiverse axioms
entry.summary: If ZFC is consistent, then the collection of countable computably saturated models of ZFC satisfies all of the Multiverse Axioms introduced by Hamkins.

entry.title: Maximum VC families
entry.summary: Maximum VC classes which are stable in the sense of model theory are characterized.

entry.title: Proposing new higher-gap morasses
entry.summary: I propose a notion of $(\omega_1,\beta)$-morass for the case $\omega_1 \leq \beta$.
entry.arxiv:comment: accepted for Far East Journal of Mathematical Sciences

entry.title: The existence of a near-unanimity function is decidable
entry.summary: We prove that the following problem is decidable: given a finite set of relations, decide whether this set admits a near-unanimity function.

entry.title: On ω-categorical, generically stable groups
entry.summary: We prove that each \omega-categorical, generically stable group is solvable-by-finite.

entry.title: Ultrafilters in Reverse Mathematics
entry.summary: We extend theories of reverse mathematics by a non-principal ultrafilter, and show that these are conservative extensions of the usual theories ACA0, ATR0, and Pi11-Comprehension.

entry.title: Oscillations and their applications in partition calculus
entry.summary: Oscillations are a powerful tool for building examples of colorings witnessing negative partition relations. We survey several results illustrating the general technique and present a number of applications.

entry.title: The Automorphism Group of a Resplendent Model
entry.summary: The first-order theory of the automorphism group of an infinite resplendent model in a finite language is undecidable.

entry.title: Categories of imaginaries for definable additive categories
entry.summary: We develop some aspects of the model theory of additive structures, with particular emphasis on the abelian category of pp-imaginaries.

entry.title: On ω-categorical, generically stable groups and rings
entry.summary: We prove that every \omega-categorical, generically stable group is nilpotent-by-finite and that every \omega-categorical, generically stable ring is nilpotent-by-finite.

entry.title: Characterizing Quantifier Extensions of Dependence Logic
entry.summary: We characterize the expressive power of extensions of Dependence Logic and Independence Logic by monotone generalized quantifiers in terms of quantifier extensions of existential second-order logic.

entry.title: Homeomorphisms with Small Twist
entry.summary: We extend Baumgartner's result on isomorphisms of aleph_1 dense subsets of the reals R in two ways: First, the function can be made to be absolutely continuous. Second, one can replace R by R^n.

entry.title: On algorithmic decidability of the square-free word problem relative to a system of two defining relations
entry.summary: The square-free word problem relative to a system of two defining relations is decidable.

entry.title: Stabilité et simplicité positive
entry.summary: We study extensions universal positive model theory. And we continue the study of stability and simplicity already initiated by Ben Yaacov.

entry.title: An inner model proof of the strong partition property of δ^2_1
entry.summary: We prove the strong partition property for \delta^2_1 using methods from inner model theory.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Notre Dame J. Formal Logic 55, no. 4 (2014), 563-568

entry.title: The core model induction beyond $L(\mathbb{R})$: non-tame mouse from PFA
entry.summary: We show that PFA implies that there is a non-tame mouse.

entry.title: The problem of Horn and Tarski
entry.summary: In 1948 A. Horn and A. Tarski asked whether the notions of a \sigma-finite cc and a \sigma-bounded cc ordering are equivalent. We give a negative answer to this question.

entry.title: Avoiding Rational Distances
entry.summary: We show that for any set of reals X there is a subset Y such X and Y have same Lebesgue outer measure and the distance between any two distinct points in Y is irrational.

entry.title: Model Theory
entry.summary: An essay on Model Theory: Why am I interested in model theory? What are, in my opinion, the most challenging problems in model theory?

entry.title: Convergence on surreals
entry.summary: Using the sign expansion of the surreal numbers, we give a possible notion of convergence for surreal sequences.

entry.title: The fundamentals of relations language mathematics
entry.summary: The fundamentals of formal logic, theory of sets and mathematical structures are narrated in terms of relations language.

entry.title: Products of rough finite state machines
entry.summary: In this paper, we introduce the concept of several products of rough finite state machines. We establish their relationships through coverings and investigate some algebraic properties for these products.

entry.title: Rigidity, internality and analysability
entry.summary: We prove a version of Hrushovski's socle lemma for rigid groups in an arbitrary simple theory.

entry.title: Relative D-groups and differential Galois theory in several derivations
entry.summary: The Galois theory of logarithmic differential equations with respect to relative D-groups in partial differential-algebraic geometry is developed.

entry.title: Atomic polyadic algebras of infinite dimension are completely representable
entry.summary: We show that atomic polyadic algebras of infinite dimensions are completely representable

entry.title: The class of infinite dimensional quasipolaydic equality algebras is not finitely axiomatizable over its diagonal free reducts
entry.summary: We show that the class of infinite dimensional quasipolaydic equality algebras is not finitely axiomatizable over its diagonal free reducts

entry.title: Logic Blog 2012
entry.summary: The 2012 logic blog has focussed on the following: Randomness and computable analysis/ergodic theory; Systematizing algorithmic randomness notions; Traceability; Higher randomness; Calibrating the complexity of equivalence relations from computability theory and algebra.

entry.title: Interpolation in many valued predicate logics using algebraic logic
entry.summary: Using polyadic MV algebras, we show that many predicate many valued logics have the interpolation property.
entry.arxiv:comment: 49 pages. arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1304.0707

entry.title: Neat atom structures
entry.summary: An atom structure is neat if there an algebra based on this atom structure in Nr_nCA_{\omega}. We show that this class is not elementary
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1302.1368

entry.title: Representation theorems in modal logic using algebraic logic
entry.summary: We prove several representation theorems for infinitary predicate modal logic

entry.title: On some open problems in Algebraic logic
entry.summary: Several open problems in algebraic logic are solved.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1302.1368, arXiv:1303.7386, arXiv:1301.5850, arXiv:1304.0619, arXiv:1304.0785, arXiv:1304.0883

entry.title: A short proof of the thumbtack lemma
entry.summary: We give a short proof of the main algebraic result of \cite{zilber2006covers}, also known as the `thumbtack lemma'.

entry.title: Excellence and uncountable categoricity of Zilber's exponential fields
entry.summary: We prove that Zilber's class of exponential fields is quasiminimal excellent and hence uncountably categorical, filling two gaps in Zilber's original proof.

entry.title: A machine that knows its own code
entry.summary: We construct a machine that knows its own code, at the price of not knowing its own factivity.

entry.title: Forcing of infinity and algebras of distributions of binary semi-isolating formulas for strongly minimal theories
entry.summary: We apply a general approach for distributions of binary isolating and semi-isolating formulas to the class of strongly minimal theories.

entry.title: Priority arguments via true strages
entry.summary: We describe a variation of Ash's $\eta$-system, and give a new proof of Ash's metatheorem. As an application, we prove a generalization of Ash and Knight's theorem on pairs of structures.

entry.title: On substitution algebras of permutations
entry.summary: The subject of this paper is a simulation to that in [1] but here we consider substitutions corresponding to transpositions instead of replacements.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:1302.3043

entry.title: Ultraproducts as a tool for first-order inexpressibility in the finite and infinite
entry.summary: Ultraproducts are a well-known tool in the classical model theory of first-order logic. We explore their uses in the context of finite model theory.

entry.title: The affine and projective groups are maximal
entry.summary: We show that the groups AGL_n(Q) and PGL_n(Q), seen as closed subgroups of S_{\infty}, are maximal-closed.

entry.title: A Simple Proof of the Fourier Inversion Theorem Using Nonstandard Analysis
entry.summary: We give a simple proof of the Fourier Inversion Theorem, using the methods of nonstandard analysis.

entry.title: Compactness in singular cardinals revisited
entry.summary: This is the second combinatorial proof of the compactness theorem for singular from 1977. In fact it gives a somewhat stronger theorem.

entry.title: On reaping number having countable cofinality
entry.summary: We prove that if the bounding number (d) is bigger than the reaping number (r), then the latter has uncountable cofinality.

entry.title: A note on Autoreducibility for Infinite Time Register Machines and parameter-free Ordinal Turing Machines
entry.summary: We propose a notion of autoreducibility for infinite time computability and explore it and its connection with a notion of randomness for infinite time machines.

entry.title: Scott rank of Polish metric spaces
entry.summary: Following the work of Friedman, Koerwien, Nies and Schlicht we positively answer their question whether the Scott rank of Polish metric spaces is countable.

entry.title: Restructuring Logic
entry.summary: The outline of a programme for restructuring mathematical logic. We explain what we mean by "restructuring" and carry out exemplary parts of the programme.

entry.title: Logic Blog 2011
entry.summary: This year's logic blog has focussed on: 1. Demuth randomness 2. traceability 3. The connection of computable analysis and randomness 4. $K$-triviality in metric spaces.

entry.title: Boole's Method I. A Modern Version
entry.summary: A rigorous, modern version of Boole's algebra of logic is presented, based partly on the 1890s treatment of Ernst Schroder.

entry.title: On Martin's Pointed Tree Theorem
entry.summary: We investigate the reverse mathematics strength of Martin's pointed tree theorem (MPT) and one of its variants, weak Martin's pointed tree theorem (wMPT).

entry.title: Indefiniteness in semi-intuitionistic set theories: On a conjecture of Feferman
entry.summary: The paper proves a conjecture of Solomon Feferman concerning the indefiniteness of the continuum hypothesis relative to a semi-intuitionistic set theory.

entry.title: An introduction to multiple gaps
entry.summary: This is an introductory article to the theory of multiple gaps.

entry.title: Representing Scott sets in algebraic settings
entry.summary: We prove that for every Scott set $S$ there are $S$-saturated real closed fields and models of Presburger arithmetic.

entry.title: Non-predetermined Model Theory
entry.summary: This article introduce a new model theory call non-predetermined model theory where functions and relations need not to be determined already and they are determined through time.

entry.title: A categorical semantic for the Typed Epsilon Calculus
entry.summary: We show that every boolean category satisfying AC provides a categorical semantic of the typed Epsilon calculus.

entry.title: Implicitly definable generalized quantifiers
entry.summary: We give a new elementary proof of the main theorem of [Fef12]: Quantifiers implicitly definable in pure second-order logic equipped with Henkin semantics implies are (explicitly) definable in first-order logic.

entry.title: Iteration of Semiproper Forcing Revisited
entry.summary: We present a method for iterating semiproper forcing which uses side conditions and is inspired by the technique recently introduced by Neeman.

entry.title: Lectures on the Epsilon Calculus
entry.summary: Notes to lectures on the epsilon calculus, covering axioms, semantics, completeness, and the first epsilon theorem.

entry.title: On the (non) superstable part of the free group
entry.summary: In this short note we prove that a definable set $X$ over $\mathbb F_n$ is superstable only if $X(\mathbb F_n)=X(\mathbb F_{\omega})$.

entry.title: Imaginaries in bounded pseudo real closed fields
entry.summary: The main result of this paper is that if M is a bounded PRC field then Th(M) eliminates imaginaries in the language of rings expanded by constant symbols.

entry.title: Definability and continuity of the SU-rank in unidimensional supersimple theories
entry.summary: We prove, in particular, that in a supersimple unidimensional theory the $SU$-rank is continuous and the $D$-rank is definable.

entry.title: Direct twisted Galois stratification
entry.summary: The theory ACFA admits a primitive recursive quantifier elimination procedure. It is therefore primitive recursively decidable.

entry.title: Hypernatural Numbers as Ultrafilters
entry.summary: In this paper we present a use of nonstandard methods in the theory of ultrafilters and in related applications to combinatorics of numbers.

entry.title: On the notions of dimension and transcendence degree for models of ZFC
entry.summary: We define notions of generic dimension and generic transcendence degree between models of ZFC and give some examples.

entry.title: On the notion of generic cut for models of ZFC
entry.summary: We define the notion of generic cut between models of ZFC and give some examples.

entry.title: Towards an Effective Theory of Absolutely Continuous Measures
entry.summary: We give a constructive, metastable formulation of a theorem about the exchange of limits for convergent sequence $L^1$ functions. A crucial tool is a one-dimensional version of Szemeredi's regularity lemma for $L^1$ functions.

entry.title: Axiomatizing some small classes of set functions
entry.summary: In this note we axiomatize the classes of rudimentary functions, primitive recursive functions, safe recursive set functions, and predicatively computable functions.

entry.title: An axiomatic system for STIT imagination logic
entry.summary: We formulate a Hilbert-style axiomatic system for STIT logic of imagination recently proposed by H. Wansing and prove its completeness by the method of canonical models.

entry.title: PFA and precipitousness of the nonstationary ideal
entry.summary: We apply Neeman's method of forcing with side conditions to show that PFA does not imply the precipitousness of the nonstationary ideal on $\omega_1$.

entry.title: Mathematical Structures defined by Identities III
entry.summary: We extend the theory (formal part only} of algebras with one binary operation (our paper arXiv:math/0110333v1 [math.RA] 31 Oct 2001) to algebras with several operations of any arity.

entry.title: On the definability of rational integers in a class of rings
entry.summary: We provide a sufficient condition for a polynomial ring, not necessarily commutative, to have a first-order definition for the rational integers.

entry.title: Solvable Lie groups definable in o-minimal theories
entry.summary: In this paper we completely characterize solvable real Lie groups definable in o-minimal expansions of the real field.

entry.title: Definability lattice for addition of rationals
entry.summary: In the present paper we discuss the lattice of reducts of $\langle \mathbb{Q}, \{$+$\} \rangle$

entry.title: $omega_{1}$ under $Pi_{1}$-Collection
entry.summary: We describe a proof-theoretic bound on $Sigma_{2}$-definable countable ordinals in Kripke-Platek set theory with $Pi_{1}$-Collection and the existence of $omega_{1}$.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:1101.5660

entry.title: Stable forking and imaginaries
entry.summary: We prove that a theory $T$ has stable forking if and only if $T^\mathrm{eq}$ has stable forking.

entry.title: Hindman's theorem and idempotent types
entry.summary: Motivated by a question of Di Nasso, we prove that Hindman's theorem is equivalent to the existence of idempotent types in countable complete extensions of Peano Arithmetic.

entry.title: $Σ^0_3$ determinacy and ${\mathbfΠ}^1_2$ monotone induction
entry.summary: Building on recent work of Philip Welch, we prove that (lightface) $\Sigma^0_3$ determinacy is equivalent to the existence of a wellfounded model satisfying the axiom scheme of (boldface) $\mathbf{\Pi}^1_2$ monotone induction.

entry.title: Dense free sets
entry.summary: We prove the existence of infinite dense free sets (in the usual topology) for set mappings on the reals, under reasonable assumptions.

entry.title: Computable randomness and monotonicity
entry.summary: We show that $z\in\R^n$ is computably random if and only if every computable monotone function on $\R^n$ is differentiable at $z$.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1410.8578

entry.title: IKP and Friends
entry.summary: The basics of Intuitionistic Kripke-Platek set theory are developed, and some independence results among related classically equivalent theories are shown using Kripke models.

entry.title: CZF and Second Order Arithmetic
entry.summary: CZF + Separation is shown to be equiconsistent with second-order arithmetic, using realizability.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Annals of Pure and Applied Logic, 141 (2006), pp. 29-34

entry.title: Groups in NTP2
entry.summary: We prove the existence of abelian, solvable and nilpotent definable envelopes for groups definable in models of an NTP2 theory.

entry.title: Implicational Completeness
entry.summary: We present a proof of completeness for the implicational propositional calculus, based on a variant of the Lindenbaum procedure.

entry.title: Infinite irredundant equational axiomatisability for a finite monoid
entry.summary: It is shown that a finite monoid can have an infinite irredundant basis of equations.

entry.title: The Peirce axiom scheme and suprema
entry.summary: We present equivalents to the Peirce axiom scheme and highlight its relevance for pairwise suprema.

entry.title: Note on Representing $\aleph_0$-categorical Linear Orders
entry.summary: These notes find a canonical representation of the $\aleph_0$-categorical linear orders based on Joseph Rosenstein's description. A unique minimal representation, called the normal form, is obtained.
entry.arxiv:comment: Short notes on a simple problem

entry.title: Pseudofinite Mc-groups
entry.summary: A pseudofinite group satisfying the uniform chain condition on centralizers up to finite index has a big finite-by-abelian subgroup.

entry.title: Q-tableaux for Implicational Propositional Calculus
entry.summary: We study $Q$-tableaux and axiom systems that they engender, producing a new proof that the Implicational Propositional Calculus is complete.

entry.title: A note on bases of admissible rules of proper axiomatic extensions of Lukasiewicz logic
entry.summary: In this note we prove that single-conclusion admissible rules of any proper axiomatic extension of the infnite valued Lukasiewicz logic are finitely based.

entry.title: PCF: The advanced PCF theorems
entry.summary: This is a revised version of Sh:430, section 6.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:math/9610226

entry.title: Fields definable in the free group
entry.summary: We prove that no infinite field is definable in the theory of the free group

entry.title: Some algebraic equivalent forms of $\mathbb{R} \subseteq L$
entry.summary: We study $\Sigma^1_2$ definable counterparts for some algebraic equivalent forms of the Continuum Hypothesis. All turn out to be equivalent to "all reals are constructible".

entry.title: First-Order Modal Logic: Frame Definability and Lindström Theorems
entry.summary: This paper involves generalizing the Goldblatt-Thomason and the Lindstr\"om characterization theorems to first-order modal logic.

entry.title: The axiom of choice, co-comprehension schema and redundancies in triposes
entry.summary: We study the role of the axiom of choice and co-comprehention in second order encoding of first order predicates logic

entry.title: Analysis of a Double Kruskal Theorem
entry.summary: The strength of an extension of Kruskal's Theorem to certain pairs of cohabitation trees is calibrated.

entry.title: Structural Properties of ${\cal R}_2$ Part I
entry.summary: This is the first of two papers establishing structural properties of ${\cal R}_2$.

entry.title: Structural Properties of ${\cal R}_2$ Part II
entry.summary: This is the second of two papers establishing structural properties of ${\cal R}_2$.

entry.title: Simultaneous stationary reflection and square sequences
entry.summary: We investigate the relationship between weak square principles and simultaneous reflection of stationary sets.

entry.title: The finite representation property fails for composition and intersection
entry.summary: The title theorem is proved by example: an algebra of binary relations, closed under intersection and composition, that is not isomorphic to any such algebra on a finite set.

entry.title: On non-separable growths of omega supporting measures
entry.summary: We present several $\mathsf{ZFC}$ examples of compactifications $\gamma\omega$ of $\omega$ such that their remainders $\gamma\omega\backslash\omega$ are nonseparable and carry strictly positive measures.

entry.title: A constructive method for linear extensions of Zadeh's fuzzy order
entry.summary: In this paper, we give a constructive method for linear extensions of Zadeh's fuzzy orders. We also characterize Zadeh's fuzzy orders by their linear extensions.

entry.title: Tableaux for First Order Logic of Proofs
entry.summary: In this paper we present a tableau proof system for first order logic of proofs FOLP. We show that the tableau system is sound and complete with respect to Mkrtychev models of FOLP.

entry.title: Modular Models for Intuitionistic Justification Logic
entry.summary: We present the logic iJT4, which is an explicit version of intuitionistic S4 and establish soundness and completeness with respect to modular models.

entry.title: Can you take Toernquist's inaccessible away?
entry.summary: We prove that ZF+DC+"There are no mad families" is equiconsistent with ZFC.

entry.title: A Borel maximal eventually different family
entry.summary: We construct a Borel maximal eventually different family.

entry.title: Cut-elimination for SBL
entry.summary: In this paper we give a terminating cut-elimination procedure for a logic calculus SBL. SBL corresponds to the second order arithmetic Pi^{1}_{2}-Separation and Bar Induction.

entry.title: Maximal independent sets in Borel graphs and large cardinals
entry.summary: We construct a Borel graph G such that ZF+DC+"There are no maximal independent sets in G" is equiconsistent with ZFC+"There exists an inaccessible cardinal".

entry.title: Deciding the Chromatic Numbers of Algebraic Hypergrahs
entry.summary: For each infinite cardinal k, the set of algebraic hypergraphs having chromatic number no larger than k is decidable.

entry.title: In Cohen generic extension, every countable OD set of reals belongs to the ground model
entry.summary: It is true in the Cohen generic extension of L, the constructible universe, that every countable ordinal-definable set of reals belongs to L.

entry.title: $\infty$-definable Subsemigroups of $M_2(\mathbb{C})$
entry.summary: We describe the $\infty$-definable subsemigroups of $M_2(\mathbb{C})$ and show directly that they are intersections of definable subsemigroups.

entry.title: Supercompact Extender Based Magidor-Radin Forcing
entry.summary: The extender based Magidor-Radin forcing is being generalized to supercompact type extenders.

entry.title: Reverse mathematics of the relativised fast growing hierarchy
entry.summary: A short note on the reverse mathematical status of the totality of the relativised fast growing hierarchy.

entry.title: Sprague-Grundy theory in bounded arithmetic
entry.summary: In this paper, we formalize Sprague-Grundy theory for combinatorial games in bounded arithmetic. We show that in the presence of Sprague-Grundy numbers, a fairly weak axioms capture PSPACE.

entry.title: Binary simple homogeneous structures
entry.summary: We describe all binary simple homogeneous structures M in terms of 0-definable equivalence relations on M, which "coordinatize" M and control dividing, and extension properties that respect these equivalence relations.

entry.title: A Borel maximal cofinitary group
entry.summary: We construct a Borel maximal cofinitary group.

entry.title: Special Aronszajn Tree Property
entry.summary: Assuming the existence of a proper class of supercompact cardinals, we force that for every regular cardinal $\kappa$, there are $\kappa^+$-Aronszajn trees and all such trees are special.

entry.title: Problems 85 and 87 of Birkhoff's "Lattice theory"
entry.summary: We solve problems 85 a(nd 87 from Birkhoff's book "Lattice Theory" (3rd edition)

entry.title: Lightface mice with finitely many Woodin cardinals from optimal determinacy hypotheses
entry.summary: The determinacy of lightface $\Delta^1_{2n+2}$ and boldface $\boldsymbol{\Pi}^1_{2n+1}$ sets implies the existence of an $(\omega, \omega_1)$-iterable $M_{2n+1}^{\#}$.

entry.title: On the existence of a strong minimal pair
entry.summary: We show that there is a strong minimal pair in the computably enumerable Turing degrees.

entry.title: Arithmetic, Infinite Trees, and Second-order Subsystems: Notes and Observations
entry.summary: Work in progress concerning alternative formalizations of arithmetic.
entry.arxiv:comment: This is work is progress which has been posted here for easier reference when discussing the work with others

entry.title: Higher Commutator Theory for Congruence Modular Varieties
entry.summary: We develop the basic properties of the higher commutator for congruence modular varieties.

entry.title: Weak König's lemma implies the uniform continuity theorem: a direct proof
entry.summary: We show in Bishop's constructive mathematics---in particular, using countable choice---that weak K\"{o}nig's lemma implies the uniform continuity theorem.

entry.title: Constructing the demand function of a strictly convex preference relation
entry.summary: We give conditions under which the demand function of a strictly convex preference relation can be constructed.

entry.title: Retracing Cantor's first steps in Brouwer's company
entry.summary: We prove intuitionistic versions of the classical theorems saying that all countable closed subsets of $[-\pi,\pi]$ and even all countable subsets of $[-\pi,\pi]$ are sets of uniqueness.

entry.title: A Comment on Argumentation
entry.summary: We use the theory of defaults and their meaning of [GS16] to develop (the outline of a) new theory of argumentation.

entry.title: Linear Hyperdoctrines and Comodules
entry.summary: In this exposition, we get examples of what is called a "linear hyperdoctrine", based on categories of comodules indexed by coalgebras. This structures can model first order linear logic.

entry.title: On a strengthening of Kotlarski's theorem
entry.summary: Kotlarski's theorem (see H. Kotlarski. Bounded Induction and Satisfaction Classes. Mathematical Logic Quarterly, vol. 32, 31-34, 1986, P. 531--544.) formalized in $WKL_0$.
entry.arxiv:comment: In Russian. The English version will follow soon

entry.title: We belong together? A plea for modesty in modal plural logic
entry.summary: A sceptical examination of the motivations for strong modal plural logics.

entry.title: A proposition is the (homotopy) type of its proofs
entry.summary: An introduction and survey of homotopy type theory in honor of W.W. Tait.

entry.title: From Strings to Sets
entry.summary: A complete proof is given of relative interpretability of Adjunctive Set Theory with Extensionality in an elementary concatenation theory.

entry.title: Keisler's Order is Not Linear, Assuming a Supercompact
entry.summary: We show that Keisler's order is not linear, assuming the existence of a supercompact cardinal.

entry.title: Calculating the closed ordinal Ramsey number $R^{cl}(ω\cdot 2,3)^2$
entry.summary: We show that $R^{cl}(\omega\cdot 2,3)^2$ is equal to $\omega^3\cdot 2$.

entry.title: A characterization of the canonical extension of Boolean homomorphisms
entry.summary: The aim of this article is to obtain a characterization of the canonical extension of Boolean homomorphisms via the Stone-\v{C}ech compactification.

entry.title: The Ziegler spectrum of the ring of entire complex valued functions
entry.summary: We will describe the Ziegler spectrum of the ring of entire complex valued functions

entry.title: Bad Groups
entry.summary: There is no bad group of Morley rank 2n+1 with an abelian Borel subgroup of Morley rank n. In particular, there is no bad group of Morley rank 3 (O. Fr{\'e}con).

entry.title: The Commutator as Least Fixed Point of a Closure Operator
entry.summary: We present a description of the (non-modular) commutator, inspired by that of Kearnes in~\cite[p.~930]{MR1358491}, that provides a simple recipe for computing the commutator.

entry.title: Ordered Monoids: Languages and Relations
entry.summary: We give a finite axiomatization for the variety generated by relational, integral ordered monoids. As a corollary we get a finite axiomatization for the language interpretation as well.

entry.title: A Note on McGee's ω-Inconsistency Result
entry.summary: In this note we show that McGee's {\omega}-inconsistency result can be derived from L\"ob's theorem.

entry.title: Measure Algebras
entry.summary: A Boolean $\sigma$-algebra $B$ is a measure algebra if and only if it is weakly distributive and uniformly concentrated.
entry.arxiv:comment: Notes for the 2016 Winter School in Hejnice. Not for publication

entry.title: Measures on Boolean algebras
entry.summary: We present a necessary and sufficient condition for a Boolean algebra to carry a finitely additive measure.

entry.title: Convergence and submeasures in Boolean algebras
entry.summary: A Boolean algebra carries a strictly positive exhaustive submeasure if and only if it has a sequential topology that is uniformly Frechet.

entry.title: Universal theories and compactly expandable models
entry.summary: Our aim is to solve a quite old question on the difference between expandability and compact expandability. Toward this, we further investigate the logic of countable cofinality.

entry.title: Two Simple Facts about Non-AC Forcing
entry.summary: We make two simple observations about properties of forcing notions without AC, one of which answers an open question.

entry.title: On Kuratowski's partitions in Ellentuck topology
entry.summary: We show that large sets in Ellentuck topology (i.e. sets which are not nowhere Ramsey) do not admit Kuratowski's partition. The similar result is true for the Sacks real forcing.

entry.title: The short mathematical proof of Frankiewicz - Kunen theorem
entry.summary: In this paper there is proved without any metamathematical techniques that the existence of precipitous ideals immediately follows from Kuratowski partitions.

entry.title: The Way of the Infinitesimal
entry.summary: A short tutorial on non-standard analysis, made in particular for people working in the Categorical Quantum Mechanics crowd.

entry.title: I0 and rank-into-rank axioms
entry.summary: Just a survey on I0: The basics, some things known but never published, some things published but not known.

entry.title: A universe with no ordinal-definable, stationary, co-stationary subset of $ω_1$
entry.summary: It is shown that the existence of a measurable cardinal is equiconsistent to a model of ZFC in which there is no ordinal-definable, stationary, costationary subset of $\omega_1$

entry.title: An invitation to model theory and C*-algebras
entry.summary: We present an introductory survey to first order logic for metric structures and its applications to C*-algebras.

entry.title: On Some Properties of Shelah Cardinals
entry.summary: We present several results concerning Shelah cardinals.

entry.title: Model-theoretic Characterizations of Large Cardinals
entry.summary: We consider model-theoretic characterizations of large cardinals, especially in terms of the compactness for omitting types (previously used by Benda to characterize supercompacts).

entry.title: Martin's maximum and the non-stationary ideal
entry.summary: We prove that under Martin's maximum the non-stationary ideal over $\aleph_1$ is almost weakly Laver.

entry.title: Ramsey Theory on Generalized Baire Space
entry.summary: We show that although the Galvin-Prikry Theorem does not hold on generalized Baire space with the standard topology, there are similar theorems which do hold on generalized Baire space with certain coarser topologies.

entry.title: A new look at interpretability and saturation
entry.summary: We investigate the interpretability ordering $\trianglelefteq^*$ using generalized Ehrenfeucht-Mostowski models. This gives a new approach to proving inequalities and investigating the structure of types.

entry.title: Pure $Σ_2$-Elementarity beyond the Core
entry.summary: We display the entire structure ${\cal R}_2$ coding $\Sigma_1$- and $\Sigma_2$-elementarity on the ordinals. This leads to first steps into analyzing pure $\Sigma_3$-elementary substructures.

entry.title: Sheva-Sheva-Sheva: Large Creatures
entry.summary: We develop the theory of the forcing with trees and creatures for an inaccessible lambda continuing Ros{\l}anowski and Shelah math.LO/9807172, math.LO/9909115. To make a real use of these forcing notions (that is to iterate them without collapsing cardinals) we need suitable iteration theorems, and those are proved as well. (In this aspect we continue Ros{\l}anowski and Shelah math.LO/9906024.)

entry.title: On our paper `Almost Free Splitter', a correction
entry.summary: Let R be a subring of Q and recall from math.LO/9910161 that an R-module G is a splitter if Ext_R(G,G)=0. We correct the statement of Main Theorem 1.5 in math.LO/9910161. Assuming CH any aleph_1$-free splitter of cardinality aleph_1 is free over its nucleus as shown in math.LO/9910161. Generally these modules are very close to being free as explained below. This change follows from math.LO/9910161 and is due to an incomplete proof (noticed thanks to Paul Eklof) in the first section of math.LO/9910161. Assuming the negation of CH, in Shelah [Sh:F417] (work in progress) it will be shown that under Martin's axiom these splitters are free indeed. However there are models of set theory having non-free aleph_1-free splitter of cardinality aleph_1.

entry.title: Successors of singular cardinals and coloring theorems. I
entry.summary: We investigate the existence of strong colorings on successors of singular cardinals. This work continues Section 2 of [Sh:413] (math.LO/9809199), but now our emphasis is on finding colorings of pairs of ordinals, rather than colorings of finite sets of ordinals.

entry.title: Towards Martin's Minimum
entry.summary: We show that it is consistent with MA + the negation of CH, that the Forcing Axiom fails for all forcing notions in the class of omega^omega-bounding forcing notions with norms of "Norms on possibilities I: forcing with trees and creatures"(by Roslanowski and Shelah - math.LO/9807172).

entry.title: Countable structure does not have a free uncountable automorphism group
entry.summary: Solecki proved that the group of automorphisms of a countable structure cannot be an uncountable free abelian group. See more in Just, Shelah and Thomas math.LO/0003120 where as a by product we can say something on on uncountable structures. We prove here the following Theorem: If A is a countable model, then Aut(M) cannot be a free uncountable group.

entry.title: Universal forcing notions and ideals
entry.summary: The main result of this paper is a partial answer to [math.LO/9909115, Problem 5.5]: a finite iteration of Universal Meager forcing notions adds generic filters for many forcing notions determined by universality parameters. We also give some results concerning cardinal characteristics of the sigma-ideals determined by those universality parameters.

entry.title: FPL may be equivalent to FO but not equivalent to PFP
entry.summary: Given a class of finite models we would like to expand each model (allowing new elements but the old universe is a separate sort), making the expressive power of LFP (least fix point logic) and PFP (inductive logic) similar while not changing the expressive power of FO (first order logic). This continues in math.LO/9411235.

entry.title: Categoricity may fail late
entry.summary: We build an example that generalizes math.LO/9201240 to uncountable cases. In particular, our example yields a sentence psi in L_{(2^lambda)^+, omega} that is categorical in lambda, lambda^+, ..., lambda^{+k} but not in beth_{k+1}(lambda)^+. This is connected with the Los Conjecture and with Shelah's own conjecture and construction of excellent classes for the psi in L_{omega_1,omega} case.

entry.title: Strongly dependent theories
entry.summary: We further investigate the class of models of a strongly dependent (first order complete) theory T, continuing math.LO/0406440. If |A|+|T|<= mu, I subseteq C, |I| >=beth_{|T|^+}(mu) then some J subseteq I of cardinality mu^+ is an indiscernible sequence over A .

entry.title: Reasonably complete forcing notions
entry.summary: We introduce more properties of forcing notions which imply that their lambda-support iterations are lambda-proper, where lambda is an inaccessible cardinal. This paper is a direct continuation of section A.2 of math.LO/0210205. As an application of our iteration result we show that it is consistent that dominating numbers associated with two normal filters on lambda are distinct.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Set theory: recent trends and applications, 195-239, Quad. Mat., 17, 2006

entry.title: An introduction to b-minimality
entry.summary: We give a survey with some explanations but no proofs of the new notion of b-minimality by the author and F. Loeser [b-minimality, J. Math. Log., 7 no. 2 (2007) 195--227, math.LO/0610183]. We compare this notion with other notions like o-minimality, C-minimality, p-minimality, and so on.

entry.title: Non-structure in lambda^{++} using instances of WGCH
entry.summary: We try to redo, improve and continue the non-structure parts in some works on a.e.c., which uses weak diamond, in lambda^+ and lambda^{++} getting better and more results and do what is necessary for the book on a.e.c. Comparing with math.LO/9805146 we make the context closer to the examples, hence hopefully improve transparency, though losing some generality. Toward this we work also on the positive theory, i.e. structure side of "low frameworks" like almost good lambda-frames.

entry.title: Perpendicular Indiscernible Sequences in Real Closed Fields
entry.summary: We investigate the behaviour of concepts from dependent theories when applied to real closed fields. Our main focus is on the concept of perpendicular indiscernible sequences, a concept first introduced in section 4 of math.LO/0009056 . This is essentially the MSc. thesis of the first author written under he guidance of the second author.

entry.title: More on SOP_1 and SOP_2
entry.summary: This paper continues math.LO/0009087. We present a rank function for NSOP_1 theories and give an example of a theory which is NSOP_1 but not simple. We also investigate the connection between maximality in the ordering <^* among complete first order theories and the (N)SOP_2 property. We complete the proof started in math.LO/0009087 of the fact that <^*-maximality implies SOP_2 and get weaker results in the other direction. The paper provides a step toward the classification of unstable theories without the strict order property.

entry.title: Large continuum, oracles
entry.summary: Our main theorem is about iterated forcing for making the continuum larger than aleph_2. We present a generalization of math.LO/0303294 which is dealing with oracles for random, etc., replacing aleph_1, aleph_2 by lambda,lambda^+ (starting with lambda=lambda^{<lambda}>aleph_1). Well, instead of properness we demand absolute c.c.c. So we get, e.g. the continuum is lambda^+ but we can get cov(meagre)=lambda. We give some applications. As in math.LO/0303294, it is a "partial" countable support iteration but it is c.c.c.

entry.title: Viva la difference I: Nonisomorphism of ultrapowers of countable models
entry.summary: We show that it is not provable in ZFC that any two countable elementarily equivalent structures have isomorphic ultrapowers relative to some ultrafilter on omega .

entry.title: On a conjecture of Tarski on products of cardinals
entry.summary: We look at an old conjecture of A. Tarski on cardinal arithmetic and show that if a counterexample exists, then there exists one of length omega_1 + omega .

entry.title: A partition theorem for pairs of finite sets
entry.summary: Every partition of [[omega_1]^{< omega}]^2 into finitely many pieces has a cofinal homogeneous set. Furthermore, it is consistent that every directed partially ordered set satisfies the partition property if and only if it has finite character.

entry.title: Constructing strongly equivalent nonisomorphic models for unsuperstable theories. Part B
entry.summary: We study how equivalent nonisomorphic models of unsuperstable theories can be. We measure the equivalence by Ehrenfeucht-Fraisse games. This paper continues [HySh:474].

entry.title: Maximal Chains in {}^ωωand Ultrapowers of the Integers
entry.summary: Various questions posed by P. Nyikos concerning ultrafilters on $\omega$ and chains in the partial order $(\omega,<^*)$ are answered. The main tool is the oracle chain condition and variations of it.

entry.title: Donder's Version of Revised Countable Support
entry.summary: Shelah introduced the revised countable support (RCS) iteration to iterate semiproperness. This was an endpoint in the search for an iteration of a weak condition, still implying that aleph1 is preserved. Dieter Donder found a better manageable approach to this iteration, which is presented here.

entry.title: $μ$-complete Souslin trees on $μ^+$
entry.summary: We prove that $\mu=\mu^{<\mu}$, $2^\mu=\mu^+$ and ``there is a non reflecting stationary subset of $\mu^+$ composed of ordinals of cofinality $<\mu$'' imply that there is a $\mu$-complete Souslin tree on $\mu^+$.

entry.title: The Genericity Conjecture
entry.summary: In this paper we produce a real r such that 0<r<0# in L-degree, yet R is NOT generic over L (for a forcing amenable to L). This answers a question of Beller-Jensen-Welch.

entry.title: Provable Pi-1-2 Singletons
entry.summary: In this note I show that a pi-1-2 singleton R of L-degree strictly between 0 and 0# can be obtained so as to be the unique solution to a pi-1-2 formula which provably has at most one solution, in the theory ZFC+(*) where (*) has the approximate strength of an ineffable cardinal.

entry.title: On closed P-sets with ccc in the space omega^*
entry.summary: It is proved that -- consistently -- there can be no ccc closed P-sets in the remainder space omega^* .

entry.title: mu-complete Suslin trees on mu^+
entry.summary: We prove that mu = mu^{< mu}, 2^mu = mu^+ and ``there is a non reflecting stationary subset of mu^+ composed of ordinals of cofinality < mu'' imply that there is a mu-complete Souslin tree on mu^+ .

entry.title: On a conjecture regarding nonstandard uniserial modules
entry.summary: We consider the question of which valuation domains (of cardinality aleph_1) have non-standard uniserial modules. We show that a criterion conjectured by Osofsky is independent of ZFC + GCH.

entry.title: On CH + 2^{aleph_1}-> (alpha)^2_2 for alpha < omega_2
entry.summary: We prove the consistency of ``CH + 2^{aleph_1} is arbitrarily large + 2^{aleph_1} not-> (omega_1 x omega)^2_2''. If fact, we can get 2^{aleph_1} not-> [omega_1 x omega]^2_{aleph_0}. In addition to this theorem, we give generalizations to other cardinals.

entry.title: Ultrafilters: Where topological dynamics = algebra = combinatorics
entry.summary: We survey some connections between topological dynamics, semigroups of ultrafilters, and combinatorics. As an application, we give a proof, based on ideas of Bergelson and Hindman, of the Hales-Jewett partition theorem.

entry.title: On hidden extenders
entry.summary: A model with a sequence of indiscernibles depending on a particular precovering set is constructed.The initial assumption is as follows: for every n<omega the set {alpha | o(alpha)=alpha^+n } is unbounded in kappa.

entry.title: Ultrafilters on omega
entry.summary: A variety of classes of naturally arising ultrafilters on omega is discussed, and the question is raised whether it is consistent that the classes are empty. Since all the classes contain the P-point ultrafilters, a negative answer would greatly extend the famous theorem of Shelah.

entry.title: The combinatorics of combinatorial coding by a real
entry.summary: We lay the combinatorial foundations for [ShSt:340] by setting up and proving the essential properties of the coding apparatus for singular cardinals. We also prove another result concerning the coding apparatus for inaccessible cardinals.

entry.title: Reverse Mathematics and Recursive Graph Theory
entry.summary: We examine a number of results of infinite combinatorics using the techniques of reverse mathematics. Our results are inspired by similar results in recursive combinatorics. Theorems included concern colorings of graphs and bounded graphs, Euler paths, and Hamilton paths.

entry.title: An Induction Principle and Pigeonhole Principles for K-Finite Sets
entry.summary: We establish a course-of-values induction principle for K-finite sets in intuitionistic type theory. Using this principle, we prove a pigeonhole principle conjectured by Benabou and Loiseau. We also comment on some variants of this pigeonhole principle.

entry.title: On a theorem of Shapiro
entry.summary: We show that a theorem of Leonid B. Shapiro which was proved under MA, is actually independent from ZFC. We also give a direct proof of the Boolean algebra version of the theorem under MA(Cohen).

entry.title: Martin's Axiom and Delta^2_1 well-ordering of the reals
entry.summary: Assuming an inaccessible cardinal kappa, there is a generic extension in which MA + 2^{aleph_0} = kappa holds and the reals have a Delta^2_1 well-ordering.

entry.title: More forcing notions imply diamond
entry.summary: We prove that the Sacks forcing collapses the continuum onto the dominating number d, answering the question of Carlson and Laver. Next we prove that if a proper forcing of the size at most continuum collapses omega_2 then it forces diamond_{omega_1} .

entry.title: OTTER Experiments in a System of Combinatory Logic
entry.summary: This paper describes some experiments involving the automated theorem-proving program OTTER in the system TRC of illative combinatory logic. We show how OTTER can be steered to find a contradiction in an inconsistent variant of TRC, and present some experimentally discovered identities in TRC.

entry.title: Universal bridge-free graphs
entry.summary: We prove that there is no countable universal $B_n$-free graph for all $n$ and that there is no countable universal graph in the class of graphs omitting all cycles of length at most $2k$ for $k\ge 2$.

entry.title: On finite rigid structures
entry.summary: The main result of this paper is a probabilistic construction of finite rigid structures. It yields a finitely axiomatizable class of finite rigid structures where no L^omega_{infty, omega} formula with counting quantifiers defines a linear order.

entry.title: The universality spectrum: Consistency for more classes
entry.summary: We deal with consistency results for the existence of universal models in natural classes of models (more exactly--a somewhat weaker version). We apply a result on quite general family to T_feq and to the class of triangle-free graphs.
